            <div class="explanation-card bad">
                <h4>❌ String Concatenation (Vulnerable)</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>User input is directly inserted into the query string</li>
                    <li>Attacker can inject SQL operators like <code>OR</code>, <code>--</code>, <code>;</code></li>
                    <li>The database interprets injected text as real SQL commands</li>
                    <li>Can bypass authentication, dump all data, or destroy tables</li>
                    <li>Input like <code>' OR '1'='1</code> makes the WHERE clause always true</li>
                    <li>No distinction between "data" and "code" — everything is one string</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-card good">
                <h4>✅ Parameterized Queries (Safe)</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Query structure is defined first, separately from user data</li>
                    <li>User input is passed as a separate parameter, never interpreted as SQL</li>
                    <li>The database engine treats the parameter as pure data, not commands</li>
                    <li>SQL operators in input become literal characters to search for</li>
                    <li>Even <code>' OR '1'='1</code> is just searched as a text string</li>
                    <li>Complete separation between "code" (query) and "data" (input)</li>
